caption:
jordan brand’s “A NOUS” mini-film series is out/live/platformed. swipe to watch our seven-part arc. 

🎥 captured in paris for jordan brand’s olympics-centric fall 2024 apparel and footwear collections. starring @ashtotheeye @kyrra.png @sam_yudat @anayce_amalys @leonie_mbk, directed by @otmanqrita, shot by @dominikpanasiuk, edited by @theolesourd. 

Art direction by @chris_barclay 🫡
Design direction by @jadelcarter 
Production ops by @mpakulski x Emily Hamlet 
Styling by @osolomon 
Narrative by me x @niag 
Interviews by me x @elehowe
Translations by @elehowe 
Creative direction by @adriano_furtado @multimultimultimulti @saadya 
Special thanks to @convoy and our countless local partners and geo friends @nordineb @kenzarnb @bdunne_ @elehowe @zoe_arich @chloeperignon @pim.caloni @thomaslelong_ @internet_jeano @kenyavallet @_karimkh @keiishah @mattmoranphoto @natalie_avo and Q. 

our narrative was inspired by movement — a la michael jordan’s first visit to the eiffel tower in 1985, where he crossed the language barrier with parisians using only a basketball and “poetic expression,” as we called it. in this game, actions indeed speak louder than words. 

our plan of action: we dug trenches and moved mountains to get this one across. and it’s just so beautiful. pressure makes diamonds 💎 fr fr. 

to anyone who touched this work: you’re all mad geniuses in my eyes. thankful for our team and whirlwind opportunity to travel and work on set for the first time. this cast x crew is best in class. 

xoxo 😘 💃🏻 🕺🏻

As seen on Nike.com and the SNKRS app, my script for Jordan Brand’s summer 2024 Air Jordan 4 campaign: “Joy Ride” starring @freeliberalist, shot in Tokyo by Tomoyuki Kawakami, and directed by Warren Cochrane.

Styling by Oliver Solomon.

Special thanks to CEKAI.
Shoutout to Dubbs for the alley-oop. 

Script and narrative themes inspired by Weezy F. 

This one was for all the people out there who feel how we feel. So let’s talk about it. I’ll ask the first question:

Do you ever get nervous?
